{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"9eb510892d1accc0c715d21128d216b2e6f74967"},"timestamp":1567503728,"title":"(agp) add scroll- region blitting","message":"When a buffer is submitted with a scroll- region, the mechanism for deferring\na release should be used, and then setup the agp_store to be in a dual-buffer\nrepack state; every time it is used and rendering, it remarks rendertarget as\ndirty, and does a block copy from buffer b into buffer a until they are the\nsame (and buffer can be freed).\n\n(this isn't necessary for text regions when we have a vertex buffer as that\ncan simply be scissored and 'scrolled' that way).","files":null}]}